When you activate the network, you do it in a way that information pr=
opagates from one neuron to the next. Basically, you go through each neuron=
, and take all of its inputs and compute its output. Then proceed to the ne=
xt until you have computed the output for every one of them. And that is on=
e &quot;activation&quot; step. In order to ensure information will flow through the e=
ntire network so it reaches all output neurons, you&#39;d do this activation a =
bunch of times. In cases where loops exist, do the activation just once, or=
 a fixed number of times. These networks don&#39;t really settle and stabilize =
on one single output pattern, they work continuously. 

